        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Authorization for GenAI APIs"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Authentication answers "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "who are you?",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "; authorization answers "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "what can you do?",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " For GenAI APIs these two questions are closely linked to business model: which models a user can call, how many tokens per day, and which endpoints are available depend on their plan, their role, and their quota state."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Unlike typical CRUD APIs where authorization is mostly about data ownership, GenAI authorization must also govern "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "cost",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " — a request to "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "claude-opus-4-8",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " costs an order of magnitude more than one to "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ". Scope and quota checks are both authorization concerns."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Authorization Models"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "attrs": {
          "src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
          "alt": "RBAC and ABAC authorization models with decision flow"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Use "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "RBAC",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " (role-based) when you have a small number of discrete tiers (free, pro, enterprise). Use "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "ABAC",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " (attribute-based) when access rules depend on combinations of user attributes (plan, org), resource attributes (model tier, data sensitivity), and context (request time, usage in the current window). Most GenAI APIs start with RBAC and add ABAC rules as the product matures."
          }
        ]
      },
